-- Colombia Stocks: Isagen, Ecopetrol, Pacific Rubiales, Canacol
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-04-04T21:46:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/colombia-stocks-isagen-pacific-rubiales-canacol-energy.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of 3 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.4 percent to 14,949.73 while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  rose 0.1 percent to 1,742.90. Colombian markets are
closed tomorrow and April 6 ahead of the Easter holiday.  Isagen SA (ISAGEN)  , a Colombian energy company, gained
for a third day, rising 0.9 percent to 2,325 pesos.  Fitch
Ratings  on April 2 changed its outlook on Isagen’s BB+ credit
rating to positive, citing the improvement in its 2011 results.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest  oil company ,
gained 0.2 percent to 5,610 pesos. The South American country’s
crude production rose 7.2 percent in March to an average of
951,000 barrels a day from 887,000 barrels a day a year earlier,
after the government increased security in response to rebel
attacks on infrastructure, the Mines and Energy Ministry said in
a statement today. In February, output fell 4.8 percent to
896,000 barrels a day after pipeline sabotage.  Oil producers fell following a drop in crude prices.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PREC)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, dropped 1.4
percent to 49,400 pesos.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based oil
company that operates fields in Colombia, plunged 4.6 percent to
1,335 pesos. The shares have plunged 18 percent since the
company said in a March 30 statement that it abandoned an
exploration well in Colombia after finding fresh water and
“slight traces” of oil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
